01:15:06.020 --> 01:15:06.661
Ad owlam.

01:15:08.181 --> 01:15:09.882
I will prepare and establish,

01:15:10.722 --> 01:15:12.884
I will appoint, equip, develop,

01:15:12.923 --> 01:15:17.186
support and sustain your offspring and

01:15:17.226 --> 01:15:19.969
that which you sow, Zera Atah.

01:15:23.310 --> 01:15:23.970
In addition,

01:15:24.211 --> 01:15:29.134
I have constructed for your throne and

01:15:29.293 --> 01:15:30.854
your seat of honor

01:15:32.337 --> 01:15:36.198
your authority on behalf of all

01:15:36.260 --> 01:15:36.899
generations,

01:15:36.939 --> 01:15:39.440
generation to generation for dwelling

01:15:39.480 --> 01:15:43.341
places and family lineage throughout time.

01:15:44.382 --> 01:15:44.802
Shalowm,

01:15:45.023 --> 01:15:48.684
pause now and contemplate those

01:15:48.703 --> 01:15:49.545
implications.

01:15:52.126 --> 01:15:53.565
I will make a bigger deal of this

01:15:53.626 --> 01:15:53.865
later,

01:15:53.886 --> 01:15:54.926
but I do want to bring this to

01:15:54.947 --> 01:15:57.207
your attention and we are nearing the end

01:15:57.247 --> 01:15:58.387
of this program.

01:15:58.408 --> 01:16:00.788
So we'll conclude with this statement from

01:16:00.849 --> 01:16:01.029
God.

01:16:02.728 --> 01:16:07.292
Kise is always just simply translated as

01:16:07.332 --> 01:16:09.372
throne.

01:16:09.413 --> 01:16:12.975
But that's not its verbal root and not

01:16:13.076 --> 01:16:15.798
always what it means.

01:16:15.819 --> 01:16:16.519
Do you know that,

01:16:17.340 --> 01:16:20.322
I think it's in the Eighty-First Mizmowr,

01:16:21.523 --> 01:16:24.886
keshe is used when Dowd says that we

01:16:24.926 --> 01:16:26.287
should blow the trumpet,

01:16:26.386 --> 01:16:30.570
sound the shofar at the new moon.

01:16:31.985 --> 01:16:32.846
And at the full moon,

01:16:33.646 --> 01:16:35.368
the new moon would be on Taruwah.

01:16:35.969 --> 01:16:37.529
The full moon would be on Pesach,

01:16:37.829 --> 01:16:42.173
on Matsah, on Bikuwrym, and on Sukah.

01:16:42.194 --> 01:16:47.577
And he says this is something that we

01:16:47.617 --> 01:16:51.399
should do and learn from, benefit from,

01:16:52.501 --> 01:16:55.262
forevermore.

01:16:55.283 --> 01:16:56.444
So it does mean full moon.

01:16:58.842 --> 01:17:01.304
And who is the full moon that's associated

01:17:01.344 --> 01:17:01.885
with dote?

01:17:02.664 --> 01:17:05.065
Who is the lesser luminary reflecting the

01:17:05.086 --> 01:17:06.306
greater luminary's light?

01:17:07.306 --> 01:17:08.627
That very same yada.

01:17:10.448 --> 01:17:12.470
But that's not all kise means.

01:17:12.510 --> 01:17:14.570
It's based upon a verb which means to

01:17:14.831 --> 01:17:17.271
cover, to conceal.

01:17:19.012 --> 01:17:21.073
What did Dowd do on Matsah

01:17:22.506 --> 01:17:26.108
He concealed our guilt by carrying it into

01:17:26.148 --> 01:17:28.890
the black hole of Sheowl to deposit it

01:17:28.909 --> 01:17:30.490
there, never to be seen again.

01:17:32.792 --> 01:17:34.573
You know the basis of Kippur and when

01:17:34.613 --> 01:17:35.395
Dowd returns?

01:17:35.914 --> 01:17:37.076
Kippur means to cover.

01:17:39.396 --> 01:17:40.837
So in his throne,

01:17:41.819 --> 01:17:45.782
there are symbols of all that God's going

01:17:45.801 --> 01:17:51.064
to do with and associated around Dowd to

01:17:51.125 --> 01:17:52.345
establish that seat of honor.

01:17:54.028 --> 01:17:55.849
And it's God that constructed all of this.

01:17:56.029 --> 01:17:56.529
He built it.

01:17:56.710 --> 01:17:58.551
He built it on behalf of every generation,

01:17:58.791 --> 01:18:01.773
every dwelling place throughout time.

01:18:01.872 --> 01:18:02.413
And he says,

01:18:02.554 --> 01:18:06.036
pause now and contemplate those

01:18:06.076 --> 01:18:06.837
implications.

01:18:07.818 --> 01:18:08.677
Well, in our next program,

01:18:08.698 --> 01:18:10.760
we're gonna return to this very passage,

01:18:11.319 --> 01:18:13.702
and then we're going to even explore more

01:18:13.742 --> 01:18:15.162
that can be deduced from it.

01:18:15.983 --> 01:18:19.104
It is a great joy to be celebrating,

01:18:20.185 --> 01:18:22.126
the Eighty-Ninth Mizmowr with you,

01:18:22.966 --> 01:18:24.766
particularly from this perspective,

01:18:24.827 --> 01:18:26.207
particularly at this time,

01:18:26.287 --> 01:18:28.108
particularly after all that we have

01:18:28.167 --> 01:18:28.488
learned.

01:18:29.208 --> 01:18:31.449
And I feel like we are literally in

01:18:31.489 --> 01:18:33.789
the middle of a deluge of understanding,

01:18:34.791 --> 01:18:35.911
and it is a joy to be able

01:18:35.930 --> 01:18:36.391
to share it.

01:18:37.311 --> 01:18:38.112
Thank you for listening.

01:18:38.452 --> 01:18:40.113
Look forward to being with you tomorrow.

01:18:40.132 --> 01:18:41.993
Hey there, thanks for tuning in.

01:18:42.014 --> 01:18:43.835
That was Fetch.

01:18:44.074 --> 01:18:47.595
Gotta run now.

01:18:47.615 --> 01:18:49.957
Catch y'all on our next podcast.